The Pentivium Pentagram (Research Description for a Blind Scholar)

The Pentivium pentagram is a five-node star structure designed to map truth and falsehood in all domains of human thought and action. Each node represents a distinct but irreducible domain; the starâ€™s edges represent the interactions between these domains.
 
1. The Five Nodes (Domains of Inquiry)

Each node has three irreducible vertices. These are not arbitrary; they are the minimal, non-overlapping elements that define the node.
â€¢	Grammar (Existence / Past)
o	Phonology (sound)
o	Morphology (form)
o	Lexicon (stored words)
â€¢	Logic (Consequence / Future)
o	Syntax (order)
o	Semantics (meaning)
o	Consequence (inference/outcome)
â€¢	Rhetoric (Expression / Present)
o	Ethos (character/credibility)
o	Pathos (emotional appeal)
o	Logos (reasoning)
â€¢	Praxis (Action / Fixed Time)
o	Intention (aim)
o	Execution (performance)
o	Feedback (result/response)
â€¢	Presence (Witness / Timelessness)
o	Awareness (perception)
o	Alignment (coherence between values and self)
o	Willpower (capacity to act)
 
2. Intra-Node Derivatives

Within each node, the three irreducibles interact in pairs.
â€¢	Example: Morphology Ã— Lexicon (in Grammar).
â€¢	Each pair splits into four possible states:
o	Virtue (both true)
o	Tilt-Left (first true, second false)
o	Tilt-Right (first false, second true)
o	Collapse (both false)

Thus, each node produces 3 derivatives Ã— 4 states = 12 cells. Across 5 nodes, this yields 60 intra-node truth cells.
 
3. Edge Derivatives (Cross-Node)

The nodes also connect to each other.
â€¢	There are 10 unique node-to-node edges (complete graph of 5 points).
â€¢	Each edge generates 6 unique irreducible pairings after collapsing redundancies.
â€¢	Total = 60 edge derivatives.

Each of these also splits into Virtue / Tilt-Left / Tilt-Right / Collapse, yielding 240 edge truth cells.
 
4. The Crown of Each Node

From the three irreducibles and their derivatives, each node produces a crown property:
â€¢	Grammar â†’ Preservation of Existence (language and memory)
â€¢	Logic â†’ Truth and Consistency
â€¢	Rhetoric â†’ Resonance and Influence
â€¢	Praxis â†’ Change and Impact
â€¢	Presence â†’ Authenticity of Being

These crowns are the â€œsummitsâ€ of each node.
 
5. Total Structure
â€¢	60 intra-node truth cells
â€¢	240 edge truth cells
â€¢	= 300 total evaluative cells in the Pentivium pentagram.

Every human act of thought, language, persuasion, action, or awareness can be mapped into this lattice as either Virtue (true), Tilt-Left, Tilt-Right, or Collapse (false).



